   "author_association" : "NONE",
   "body" : "The current `*receivedby*` RPCs filter out coinbase transactions. This doesn't seem correct since an output to your address in a coinbase transaction is receiving those coins. However, since this is potentially a breaking change this PR introduces an option `include_coinbase` that defaults to `false`. \r\n\r\nThe one exception is `listreceivedbyaddress` where the `address_filter` option is last. It is necessary to move `include_coinbase` ahead of `address_filter` so that this option can be specified without adding a filter.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/14654.",
